Structure:
SQL databases are structured and table-based;
NoSQL databases are typically document, key-value, graph, or wide-column based and are schema-flexible;

Language: 
SQL uses SQL;
NoSQL databases use various query languages or APIs.

Scalability: 
SQL scales vertically; 
NoSQL scales horizontally.

ACID vs. BASE: 
SQL databases prioritize ACID compliance;
NoSQL databases often prioritize availability and partition tolerance (BASE).
